  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">&quot;The Institute for Climate and Society is our main in-country partner for climate mitigation efforts in Brazil. The Institute evolved from the Latin America Regional Climate Initiative, a collaboration among ClimateWorks Foundation, Oak Foundation, and the Children&#x2019;s Investment Fund Foundation. The Institute has established itself as a country convener, coordinator, and re-granter, and now works with Brazilian foundations such as Arapya&#xFA; Institute. This general operating support grant seeks to improve the Institute&#x2019;s capacity to deliver their goals. Priority goals in the coming year include the implementation of Brazil&#x2019;s Intended Nationally Determined Contribution and preparing the country to host the COP25.&quot;</narrative>
  </description>
